
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-barwood-dnsext-fr-resolver-mitigations-08.txt'>
    <title>"Resolver side mitigations", George Barwood</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-barwood-dnsext-fr-resolver-mitigations-08.txt</link>
    <description>Describes mitigations against spoofing attacks on DNS, including:  (1) Repeating the query, including techniques for handling  non-deterministic responses.  (2) Prepending a random nonce to the question where a referral is  probable.  (3) Estimating the entropy available, taking into account  (a) Observed packets with incorrect IDs.  (b) The content of the cache.</description>
    <dc:date>2008-10-25T22:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
